    "B. Vertical Scaling: Benefits and Diminishing ReturnsVertical scaling improves CPU, memory, bandwidth, and storage.",
    "Systems such as Aurora Serverless v2 [1] support micro-adjustments to instance capacity.",
    "Kubernetes VPA [10] similarly adjusts pod size.However:• memory upgrades help workloads with large working sets but do nothing for skew across partitions, • CPU upgrades help compute-heavy workloads but not metadata bottlenecks, • bandwidth upgrades help replication but not compaction backlogs.Vertical scaling eventually hits ceilings and exhibits diminishing returns.",
